  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Mizrahi, ?] which was more religious, and because of that was affiliated with [?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Mizrahi. ?] He went to kibbutzim-- he went to a kibbutzim which was governed by [?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Mizrahi, ?] a more religious surrounding.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Some-- some of the children went to different places.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I went to-- first of all, I didn't know which kibbutz I should go.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one day, a selection of Hashomer [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Hatzairim ?] kibbutzim came.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was decided by them that the kibbutz Amir in [?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Galilee, ?] a rather young group of people, would be able to take 10 of the group, because they couldn't take all of them there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were only able to take 10.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Another kibbutz took another 10.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so we-- we all split up.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Joschko went to his kibbutz, Gat, in the Negev.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "By splitting up, I would like to emphasize we really never split up, because we-- we stood-- or we are still standing, in contact with-- with each other, even if it is only through the mail now.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And even if we all have glasses, and perhaps somebody is not in the very best health and we are in the-- in the 70s today, when we look out from-- with our eyes, when we see one of our people, we see only the child we were, the teenagers, whatever we did together.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We never really aged.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] We were [? real ?] good Zionists.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And when I joined the kibbutz Amir, I also joined the Palmah.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The Palmah was the Jewish underground-- how should I say-- security force.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "There was no military force.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There was no real police force, or [? something. ?] It was called-- called Palmah.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
